            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Norwegian Directorate of Immigration (UDI) has a contract with Aleris Ungplan &amp; Boi AS (Aleris) for the provision of services connected to residential and care solutions for residents in asylum centres who have special follow-up needs.</P>
               <P>The contract will be valid for 4 years and will expire in 2.2018.</P>
               <P>UDI had a competition for the service that was announced on 23.10.2017 with a subsequent contract by the expiry date of the existing contract. The competition was delayed as the competition had to be cancelled and re-announced due to technical conditions in the competition.</P>
               <P>UDI hereby announces an intention to extend the contract until the new framework agreement is signed. The contract value is estimated to be between NOK 10 000 000 - NOK 12 000 000.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="NOK">12000000.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85311200"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85311300"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Norwegian Directorate of Immigration (UDI) has a contract with Aleris Ungplan &amp; Boi AS (Aleris) for the provision of services connected to residential and care solutions for residents in asylum centres who have special follow-up needs.</P>
                  <P>The special residential and welfare system is a residential and welfare offer for residents who cannot be taken care of in an ordinary state reception centre, a reception centre with a facilitated department or a reception centre for single underage asylum seekers, due to threats and/or violent behaviour. As a rule, this applies to residents who are considered by UDI to be a threat to their surroundings. Others can also be offered a place in extraordinary circumstances, but the residents will always be persons who come under the Aliens Act § 95 1st section.</P>
                  <P>The contract will be valid for 4 years and will expire in 2.2018.</P>
                  <P>UDI had a competition for the service that was announced on 23.10.2017 with a subsequent contract by the expiry date of the existing contract. The competition was delayed as the competition had to be cancelled and re-announced due to technical conditions in the competition.</P>
                  <P>UDI hereby announces an intention to extend the contract until the new framework agreement is signed. The contract value is estimated to be between NOK 10 000 000 - NOK 12 000 000.</P>
                  <P>UDI emphasises that to find other temporary measures for the resident group would be a very bad alternative for the user group, as it will involve a considerably increased risk of the residents´ experience of safety, overview and predictability disappearing. Furthermore, this strain would be repeated after a short time as it would be a short time from when a new temporary solution is in place until the new contract and final solution is in place. The residents generally have a good score from environmental therapy, predictability, overview and known routines — something that in itself reduces conflict.</P>
                  <P>An extension is being made out of consideration to the resident group and out of consideration to the surroundings, cf. the public procurement regulations § 30-1 (3).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
