                     <P>UDI emphasises that to find other temporary measures for the resident group would be a very bad alternative for the user group, as it will involve a considerably increased risk of the residents´ experience of safety, overview and predictability disappearing. Furthermore, this strain would be repeated after a short time as it would be a short time from when a new temporary solution is in place until the new contract and final solution is in place. The residents generally have a good score from environmental therapy, predictability, overview and known routines — something that in itself reduces conflict.</P>
